<h3>TDD with TypeScript, AngularJS, and Node.js</h3>
<p>TypeScript helps to develop and maintain large web applications. Strong typing prevents from introducing bugs, but it doesnâ€™t mean we can give up on testing. In this talk I showed how we can use TDD for building web applications with TypeScript on the client side (with AngularJS) and server side (with NodeJS). I showed a few JavaScript testing frameworks (<a href="https://mochajs.org/">mocha</a>, <a href="http://jasmine.github.io/">Jasmine</a>), and showed a few tools that can make Web Developerâ€™s life easier (<a href="https://www.npmjs.com/">npm</a>, <a href="http://gulpjs.com/">gulp</a>, <a href="http://bower.io/">bower</a>, <a href="http://definitelytyped.org/tsd/">tsd</a>, <a href="http://karma-runner.github.io/0.13/index.html">karma</a>, <a href="https://angular.github.io/protractor/#/">protractor</a>).</p>
